.\" termin.al-name: history
.\" termin.al-usage: history
.\" termin.al-summary: Show this shell pane's bounded command history.
.TH HISTORY 1 "" "termin.al" "termin.al Manual"
.ftr B R
.ftr I R
.ftr BI R
.SH NAME
history \- Show this shell pane's bounded command history.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
history
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
Prints the bounded command history owned by the current shell pane. Entries are numbered from 1 in retained order and preserve the submitted command source, including quoting.
.SH OUTPUT
The history invocation is already present in the execution context and therefore appears as the final entry. Number columns widen as required.
.SH FAILURES
Any argument is rejected.
.SH LIMITS
Each shell pane retains its latest 100 submitted commands. Older entries are discarded when the bound is exceeded.
.SH NOTES
History is pane-local and survives clear(1), directory changes and pane-tree transforms while that shell pane exists. It is discarded when the pane closes or the browser page reloads, and it does not include output text.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
$ echo one
$ history
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
clear(1), pane(1), pwd(1)
